abstract: THE MURDER CASE--THE BODY IDENTIFIED AS THAT OF AN ITALIAN REFUGEE.--At 10 o'clock yesterday morning, the investigation into the mysterious murder of Monday evening was resumed, before Coroner HANFORD. abstract: ANNIVERSARY OF A MEMORABLE EVENT.--Today is the anniversary of one of the most starting crimes that ever stained the records of Philadelphia. We refer to the murder of Mrs. SHAW and Mrs. LYNCH. On the night of the 10th of March, 1853, they fell victims to the ferecity and capidity of ARTHUR SPRING, and the next morning revealed a scene, at the house in Federal-street, which we would gladly shut out from our memory.

abstract: The message from the President to-day, relative to the Black Warrior outrage, is the universal topic of conversation this evening. abstract: WHAT IS DIRT?--Old Dr. COOPER, of South Carolina, used to say to his students: Don't be afraid of a little dirt, gentlemen. What is dirt? abstract: DECEASED NEWSPAPERS.--Two of our Georgia exchanges have within the last week gone the way of all the earth. The Oglethorpe Democrat and Athens Herald are no more. We regret their fate. Both have been welcome visitors to our office. It is but a little while since another Georgia weekly, the Vote Mecum., ceased to be. And not a year since the Southwestern Georgian, published at Oglethorpe, set the example of dying.

abstract: About six weeks since, a bark belonging to New-York, from Mayumba, African coast, for Havana, put in here, pretending to be in distress. She had no cargo. The captain had a survey upon her, in hopes, it is presumed, that she would be condemned, that he might sell her, in which he was disappointed--the surveyors reporting but slight damages, and that very light repairs would put her in readiness for sea.

abstract: It would be doing tile German people great injustice for any one to suppose that a party exists among them really favorable in feeling to Russia. Indeed, public opinion and the voice of all political parties are so unanimous in their dislike, nay, in their heart-hatred to Russia, that it is idle to talk of anything like a Russian party among the various populations of the Teutonic family.

abstract: ANOTHER CANARSIE RIOTER CONVICTED.--MICHAEL McCONNELL, one of the parties engaged in the riot at Carnarsie, on the 5th of July last, was arraigned for trial in the Court of Sessions, before Judge MOORE, yesterday, on an indictment charging him with robbery, committed during the riot on that occassion, in stealing a gold watch from the person of JEREMIAH SCHENCK, who was so severely beaten on that occasion.

abstract: We have often heard of meeting a murderer on the high seas, but seldom have to record such scenes of violence as occurred, on the steamer S. F. J. Trabue, on the Mississippi River, during her recent trip from New-Orleans. As is usual, at this season of the year, the boat was crowded with deck passengers, cheifly flat-boatmen, from the Wabash, and coal-boatmen from Pittsburg.

abstract: To the Editor of the New-York Daily Times: An American has at length found favor in the eyes of the leviathan of the newspaper press, the London Times. A circumstance so unheard-of is cause for suspicion--suspicion that, unperceived by its, author, Colonel WEBB, the lauded letter bears a covert attack upon American interests.

abstract: Gov. SEYMOUR will to-morrow return to the Senate the bill for the suppression of intemperance, with his objections to its becoming a law. While deeming it his duty to make public, at the earliest moment, the conclusion at which he has are rived, the Governor has not as yet made known the reasons which he will assign for his interposition of the veto.
